author: snichol
msg: Correctly handle HTTP headers with no value (just a header name).

author: snichol
msg: Added client support for one-way calls as defined by WSDL.  The client
receives a null Envelope for the messaging API or a null Response for the
RPC API.  The RPC API was tested against a .NET server.
Based in part on a submission by Pavel Ausianik <Pavel_Ausianik@epam.com>.

author: snichol
msg: For serialization within the SOAP envelope, use Envelope.LINE_SEPARATOR as
the "line separator".  This is a constant with no platform dependency.  For
now, it is "\n" for backward compatibility, but do not rely on that!
